title: Arrived Damaged : liquid in hub locker!
text: Unfortunately Amazon in their wisdom (cough, cough) decided to ship the snowsuit in a vinyl bag with holes in it!  There was no other bag to protect the snowsuit inside vinyl bag with all the holes.  This is what happened:  Arrived in hub locker. It was the very top locker. Opened it & pulled the pkg out getting a very wet & nasty surprise at the same time. My senses were assaulted. Smells like tea tree oil. Feels like conditioner or lotion.  I can’t understand how the delivery person a) didn’t smell that mess when they shoved the pkg in b) didn’t see the mess when they shoved it in - tho if they were short I guess that would explain it bc I’m 5’10” & I didn’t see it until the pkg was in my hands. The locker was up high & dark, but I could smell it the minute I walked into the hub locker room. I happen to be extremely allergic to tea tree oil.  It’s made from mellaleuca trees which grow all over southwest Florida where I was raised.  Tho native to Australia they were used to help drain the swamps of Florida generations ago bc they soak up so much water.  It has a very distinct smell & unfortunately is frequently used as a “carrier oil” for other oils & body lotions,  shampoos, conditioners, etc., so I have to be hyper-vigilant to avoid exposure.  Instead- Last night I got to suck down Benadryl & pray my throat didn’t close while keeping my epi-pens handy.  The liquid went through the holes & onto the snowsuit as you can clearly see in the pictures.  So I guess the suit is waterproof.  Looks true to size.  Elastic appears stretchy.  I’m super annoyed that this arrived in this condition & could have easily been avoided by amazon properly wrapping it to avoid the elements whatever they may be.

title: Useless under 40 degrees.
text: Useless under 40 degrees unless you’re just running to the mailbox & back & don’t mind freezing during that jog.  Zero interior pockets so nowhere to put glasses, iPhone, etc other than the 2 exterior pockets which should be larger imo as they are the only pockets.  Seems to me like they used a too large needle with the thread in mine bc it’s like the air comes through every single hole the thread is in that they used for decoration/insulation to give it a quilted effect.  With cotton fabrics you wash it & the material will shrink around the thread & you don’t have the air coming through the too large holes made by the needle.  I usually stick with the non-quilted versions of non-cotton coats fit this reason.  It looks nice, but it does not keep me warm in northern Colorado where we dip into negative temps & have crazy high winds.  I was not impressed with it. Got it in tye try before you buy program without realizing I would have to pay for bags to return the items I tried or that I would have to drop them off at ups. I’m disabled.  I don’t drive.  So fun to pay for taxis to return stuff when Amazon has a flipping hub at my apt complex.  Why can’t they make returns simpler?  Delivered to the hub & I should be able to return it to the hub imo.  Really ticks me off I don’t get anything delivered to my door anymore since moving to an apt. As a disabled person it’s a massive pain in my tush.  Every step is agony & the stuff weighs more than I am supposed to lift.  It’s a long walk when you’re in chronic pain.  Should have sent it back with the rest bc now I’ll have to pay for another $3 bag & taxis, but I wanted to try it in colder weather since it matched the color of my boots.  My bad.  Useless in cold weather.  The other issue I noticed was I tried 3 Columbia jackets in the same size (xl) bc I like to wear fleece & layers under my coats due to the temps here & the difference in sizing was ridiculous.  This was a true xl while the other two were not.  Easily managed camisole, T-shirt, & long sleeved, very thick, fleece shirt under it.  Just does not keep you warm on its own.  It’s a spring jacket imo not winter.  It has a fuzzy fur inside & I have coke to prefer fleece lined jackets bc I have service dogs & their fur is easier to get off flat fleece than fluffy fur.

title: Not waterproof, but a very comfy shoe.
text: I purchased these bc they are supposed to be waterproof. Mine are not.  Wore them in Colorado in 36 degree weather & I can feel air coming into the toe bed so my toes were cold.  Maybe they didn’t waterproof mine all the way idk or not at all bc mine are not.  I wire regular athletic socks today, but will try them again with wool socks later.  Either way they are one of the most comfy boots I have ever worn. The cushioning is magnificent. I’m disabled & have bad knees, hips, & spine & these were the most comfy shoes I’ve probably had in my life. I say that as an LL Bean, Land’s End, Merrel, Keen, & Columbia long time wearer.  I got the baby blue color for around $40 with tax which is a great deal imo.  The only big issue is I purchased them for winter walks with my dogs so they won’t work for their intended purposes. My dilemma is whether to keep them for spring boots.  The light color means they will get dirty fast so idk.  I just know they are crazy comfy & feel wonderful on my feet. I might try them with some fleece socks too & probably just spray them with boot waterproofing.  They are like a canvas tennis shoe. The material they are made out of.  So super light which I love due to my disabilities, but I don’t think I’ll be wearing these in the back country walks bc of the color I picked. Which I picked solely based on the price. I’m cost effective not cheap lol.  I admit when I got them from the amazon locker they were so incredibly light that I expected garbage.  While these are very light they are also an excellent walking boot imo tho if you need them to be waterproofed good luck bc mine are not.  If you are sticking to plowed roads & sidewalks & avoid big drifts of snow & wear a thick wool sock these will probably work very well if you’re looking for a comfy hiking boot.  Unfortunately I need something that can go off roads into the wilderness & snow drifts bc that’s where my service dogs prefer to walk. Lol.

title: Lovely, but QA issues with sewing
text: I’ll start by saying I love this robe!  I truly do. Luckily I’d read other reviews and although normally I would immediately wash every item of clothing I purchase I decided to check the sewing and seams first. That said the quality assurance person should be fired. As you can see in the photos 2 seams are already coming undone as they were not seen properly.  There is also what I call “bobbin vomit” in several places where gobs of thread are in and around the seams and in other places there are just loose threads.  Some of the seams do not match up either. If it wasn’t for the seams that are already coming undone it is something I would normally overlook as it was close enough.  The other issue is the size. I’m 5’ 10” tall and I ordered the large/extra large as I’d read some complaints about size and especially short sleeve length. Let me tell you these sleeves will hold monkey arms!  I rolled them up twice!  They never happens to me with a large or extra large robe which I always buy big just to get the longer sleeve length. The length of time is excellent too as it is down between my calves and my ankles. I love the color. I love the robe, but due to the sewing errors as is bound to happen in mass manufacturing I am sending it back. I wish they had the sizes separated by small, medium, large, and extra large not lumping them s/m and l/xl.  I haven’t decided if I’m going to try the robe in a size smaller or just try a different robe.  If this robe was free of sewing mistakes I would have just kept it for a taller friend of mine.  It is the perfect weight. It’s not too heavy and it’s not too light. It is soft. It is fluffy. The pockets are nice and the sayin trummis a nice touch I love the hood. It was the deciding factor in my choosing this robe in the first place.  I’ll be sad to see it go as it really is an excellent robe if it didn’t have the bad seams in 2 places and the Bobbin vomit thread issues.  It’s the kind of robe you will want to snuggle and cuddle into and with someone. Two people will easily fit in this one!  I’m just afraid that if I buy the s/m that the arms will not be long enough and the robe length will be shorter too. I also hate that most s/m robe belts hit me under my breasts instead of at my natural waist and the pockets are located under each breast instead of along my hips. This robe belt fits perfectly at my waist and the pockets sit perfectly at my hips with no awkward belting or pocket maneuvering involved.  I’m really going to miss this robe!  I suspect I will end up with another one shortly, but hopefully one without flaws.

title: Just ok
text: Don't be fooled by the description. I was freezing my butt off at 40 degrees! These are very thin, so to call them "fleece-lined" feels deceptive. Not a fan! I'd rather pay for a pair of Kerrits, which are truly warm! I ordered a medium but could have sized down to small.

title: Great watch for nurses
text: Love this watch! It's perfectly petite! It's reliable, comfortable, and easy to clean - that last detail is especially important for nurses! Really happy with my purchase.

title: Perfect Ren Fest dress!
text: Absolutely gorgeous! I'm 5'1" and the dress does need to be hemmed by about 3-4 inches. In the pics, there was hem glue on the white lining, so it was easier not to step on it. It got so, so filthy at the fair but easily washed out and no ironing needed! For reference I got the size S/M, and I'm 135 lbs. I was able to cinch the waist in front and in the back.

title: FINALLY, my hat soulmate
text: I absolutely LOVE this hat. I have had a very difficult time finding a hat to fit my small head, even resorting to purchasing kid-sized fedoras. While this isn't a "petite" sized hat, I trusted the other reviewers and ordered it anyway. So glad I did! It fits great and doesn't look too big for my head. The adjustable string inside is perfect and the fabric-lined interior is comfortable - not at all itchy. I saw some people asked if the hat could be crushed. I don't think that is the best idea. Wallaroo makes another kind of hat that is meant to be crushed, but the brim is different that this one.

title: Disappointing.
text: Though these look cute on the outside, in reality these were a bad buy and not at all what I expected based on the description. For one thing, I wear a size 6-7. Knowing they run a bit small, per other reviewers, I purchased the medium (size 7-8), and my toes pressed up against the front of the slipper! Also, if you look at the photo, there is a seam at the ankle where the footie joins with the rest of the slipper. This seam was really uncomfortable, digging into my skin when I walked. The buttons, which look as though they have a function, are actually just decorative. And the worst part? That lovely soft tuft of fur you can see poking out the top of the slipper doesn't go all the way down - just to the base of your ankle. The rest of the inside is made of a plain fabric. Overall, a poorly made item that I ultimately returned.

title: They're okay.
text: Got these for my husband, he really likes the different colors and patterns, but the inside of the sock is where the quality starts to fall apart. The threads from all the patterns keep getting caught on his toes when he tries to put his feet inside them, which he reports is "super annoying". It isn't all the pairs, but several of them have this problem.

title: Ermahgerd, an ersome hert
text: You guys need to get this hat! I'm a petite adult female (lol that makes me sound like some breed of dog) and I have kind of a small head. All the adult sized hats sized small are still too large in circumference. So here is a pic of me in the hat so you can see what it looks like. I was in an Athleta fashion show, lol. I am really not made for the runway. I tried to do a little pirouette thingy and my shoes with their rubber bottoms kinda got stuck as I spun around and it looked super awkward. Anyway, I digress. The hat. The quality is good for a "made in China" item, the inner brim is not at all itchy. It's not the most ventilatory thing to wear in 190 million percent humidity, but as my mother always said, pain is the price for beauty. I also purchased the hat in another color. You really can't go wrong with this accessory! So buy it now!! :-)

title: These are the slippers of boots - totally comfortable the minute you slide your feet inside
text:
These are the slippers of boots - totally comfortable the minute you slide your feet inside.

Sizing: I normally wear a straight-up size 6.5 in boots, really no matter the brand. I like to wear a normal-thickness pair of tight athletic socks. I almost bought a size 6 after reading some of the reviews about the boots being way too large, but I ended up going with my gut and sticking with a 6.5. I'm so glad I did - they are the perfect fit. Just enough room in the toe box with socks on. I think that if you have narrow feet, the boots might feel too loose for you around the side of the foot. I have a normal width, so they felt comfortable to me. Keep in mind that you can somewhat adjust the tightness of the boot with those side button things. They are a little difficult to work with, but it's doable. If this helps, I wear a 7 in Merrell's hiking shoes, so I somewhat sized down into my usual boot size to purchase these.

Arch support: kind of meh, but not terrible either. I'd rate it somewhere in-between. You can always swap out the insoles for your custom orthotics.

Style: intended to be somewhat comfy-slouchy, so if you're looking for a more stiffly-conforming boot, I would recommend you try a different style. These have a kind of an urban mod feel to them, which I love!

title: Surprisingly disappointing
text:
As a long-time wearer of Wacoal bras, I was really excited to receive this in the mail. However, I found myself so disappointed in this bra that I sent it back to Amazon. I think I am going to spend the extra $20 to get the other model bra mentioned in other reviews! Here are the problems I had with the bra:

Material: It feels much more cheap than my other Wacoal bras. Also, there is a little ring on each bra strap that attaches it to the band, and I don't have much confidence that it will hold together.

Band: There are only 2 hook-and-eye closures on the back of the bra (I wear a 32DD). This feels insufficient compared to my other Wacoals.

Sizing: The bra, for me, runs larger than expected. Every single one of my Wacoal bras is a 32DD, and the cup size on this model is too big. I have not lost weight as I immediately put on a different Wacoal bra in the same size, and it still fits perfectly.

I am a huge proponent of Wacoal bras - just not this particular model.

I can honestly tell you that I had planned on returning these right off the bat after trying them on out of the box but then I got busy and the return window lapsed so I was stuck with what I thought were "unusable" shoes because of that narrow toe :(- HOWEVER! because I was stuck with them I thought well I mind as well walk around in them and they actually began to give some in the toe and are totally wearable and fairly comfortable once broken in a bit. PLUS after I started trying to break them in- my fiancée noticed them immediately ( and lets just say he doesn't give me a ton of shoe compliments without being asked!) and he LOVES the look of them - he always talks about them being my cute "pink shoes"... ahem... meaning I should wear them. I WISH this came in more colors as I would definitely order in a rose pink or very light aqua. The white lettering contrasts with the 'angry' message and I think gives more comedic effect that way.

title: Yikes. What you see is definitely not what you get.
text:
Terrible, Low Quality material. Would have returned it but I already washed it. Material is much thinner than it appears in photo and would probably only keep you warm if you sat in a sauna. The photo material looks like a thick polyester material you would HOPE is inner lined with fleece. Keep dreaming.

The outer material is actually a cheap cotton tee shirt-like material with an abrasive texture on inside that mimics sweats but not quite.

After two washings, the hood ties are already fraying apart at the knotted ends and have almost completely faded, even while using Cheer color guard. They definitely overpriced this product for the quality you receive. Don't bother.

I give it 3 stars because the fit is good but the color is wrong. The material is fine and the quality of the fabric seams good and like it will last.

This is a lovely very lightweight hat, the cap portion is thin and stretchy and the brim is stiff, a bit heavy compared to the rest of the hat but feels comfortable. Less like a traditional baseball hat, more like a brim with a stretchy fabric that goes around your head. Good design.

I got the slightly obnoxious high viz yellow to wear while road running and would consider getting another in a more attractive color for wearing all the time! It is definately visible though!

I did cut the stitches between the thumb hole and the hem - they just hold the seam closed, the seam itself is sewn separately so this enlarges the opening without damaging the seam. I would purchase another.

Warm and mosture wicking but the lack of a gusset is a strange choice - they ride up my but as a result.

I like the wide elastic band and infinity drawstring. They fit low on my hips but stay up well. The matte fabric is nice. These are good in the mid 20s to mid 30s.

title: good winter walking shoe
text: These are comfortable sneaker type shoes for walking outdoors in cool weather. Although they are not waterproof, they do keep out moisture if you step into a shallow puddle or walk through wet grass, etc. The upper is very soft and flexible, not stiff at all. They are a bit wide and roomy, and I have narrow feet, but I can wear them very comfortably if I tighten the laces. No issue there. I chose to add a cushioned insert, there is definitely enough space for most insoles. The shoes themselves have a pretty minimal insole, not a ton of arch support or cushion. They have nice treds on the outside but it looks like they would wear down since they aren't that deep.

title: Good for running in mild temps
text: I am 5'1" 105 lbs and ordered an xs short. Thank you under armour for selling petite sizes!! They fit great, next to skin but not restrictive. These are lightweight leggings for warm weather, we still have some 50s + 60s days and these are perfect. No issues with chaffing or discomfort, at least not at a 5k distance. Not see through.

title: Cheaply made, loose threads, thin & scratchy
text: Title says it all, really. It's thin, it's a very loose knit, there are loose threads everywhere... it's on the wider side so it won't stay up over your nose or keep your neck warm, although wearing it as a hood, around your head,  or as balakava is ok. It's more expensive than and less nice than similar products from other brands. Washing it did make it a bit softer, but I have no idea how a reputable brand that is so popular can also be so cheap and poorly made.

title: Nice running socks
text: These socks are slick to prevent blisters when running. They fit great (woman's size 7 shoe) and have some cushion but are overall very thin. Very comfortable.

title: Good gloves!
text:
I just got these, but they seem very well made and sturdy. Outdoor Research is an excellent company and I have three other items from them, all of which are well made.

I measured my hands and compared to the company's size chart before ordering. They fit great. They work well with my phone.

These are very thick gloves - heavyweight, as it says. The packaging clarifies that they are designed for 20-40F weather and can be used as a liner.

I got the cacao color which in person is a warm brownish purple/plum. It's a nice color but I bought them for warmth and fit.

title: My 3rd + 4th sets of TSLA leggins
text:
I am 5'1" and 105lbs, 24" waist 33" hips, ordered an XS.

This fit more tightly than my other pair of leggings with a pocket at the waist rather than on the leg, kind of like a compression legging, but both styles are very comfortable. They smelled a little weird out of the bag so I threw them in the wash/dry and tried them on - good fit. They are more what I would call a mid rise, coming 2.5" below my true waist. Still a comfortable rise for me. I also own a pair of TSLA XS black fleece leggings. All four leggings are squat proof and pass a flash photo test (that is, you can't see my underwear if I take a photo with the flash). I keep coming back to this brand because it's so hard to find nice, affordable leggings especially in small sizes. I wore these leggings on two 1.5 mile long walks in the heat and stayed comfortable, so I would say they are moisture wicking and good to work out in. Whether or not they are good for runs probably depends on how they fit you as you really do not want to run in leggings if there is any chaffing at all or any other fit issue. They do have flat seams that are good for running.

title: Pretty and comfortable
text: I am 5'1" 105lbs, the xs skort is comfortable, flattering, and just the right length. The shorts under are pretty short (kind of like hot pants) so not super modest but fine for normal activities where the skirt covers you most of the time. Quick dry type fabric. Basically it's well made and what I expected.

title: Lightweight but not sturdy
text: Definitely comfortable and light weight but it feels a little flimsy. Worried about durability.

title: Nice watch, good gift

title: Ok but not great
text: These earrings have a weird finish that is smooth/shiny in some areas and rough/matte in others. They don't irritate my ears and are light weight but the finish seems low quality.

title: Runs large but seems well made
text:
I have a 24" waist, ordered an xxs. They are big but i can make them work with the included belt. They are warm and seem well constructed. Due to being so big be they make a weird noise when I walk and the legs rub together. I bought these for field work on cold, damp days. I wish they sold smaller sizes. Calling pants with a 28" waist extra extra small is a little ridiculous.

I wore these into a pool of water while doing fieldwork in 40F weather. The water rolled right off the outer layer, the fleece got wet (obviously, these are pants not waders) but stayed warm and dried fast. I'm really glad to have these and I will be wearing them on future expeditions. I think they would also be good for hiking in wet, cold weather.

title: pretty watch, well made

title: good hat!

title: Ran a little too big for me (32A/B)

title: Good fit, not high rise, comfortable
text: I have a 25" waist and 32" hips and ordered the xs, which fits well - very stretchy, doesn't dig in, etc. I did not find them to be particularly high rise, maybe the style changed? They fit like normal thongs and are comfortable, they do have seams but they don't show under my leggings so I don't mind. They were comfortable and dry on my 3 mile run.

title: and it's perfect for that
text:
I bought this watch to wear to an interview, and it's perfect for that. Very small and dainty on my wrist, but still easy to read at a glance. I removed the removable link but it still a little big for my wrist, so I will probably eventually have more links removed. It is loose enough that it often turns upside down. I do have pretty small wrists, however.

I am sensitive to nickel but have not had a problem with this watch.

The band becomes completely separate when you open the clasp, making it a little harder to put on than some other watches.

It was packaged in a small red box, which I intend to keep. The watch is fastened around a small piece of foam. It's not as nice as the packaging for some of my other watches, but this watch was much less expensive so I guess you get what you pay for.

title: What's that smell?
text: Lovely items, but they smelled strongly of chemicals right out of the package. I washed on delicate cycle with cold water and line dried, that got rid of the smell.

title: Nice socks, but way too tight!
text: These socks are very very tight and ROLL DOWN. They are long enough to go all the way up my thighs but they roll down to my knees and leave a tight mark. Even when I scrunch them down around my calves they roll and leave a tight mark. I think there is some kind of elastic around the top. They might be good for someone who is very thin - I wear a 4/6. The price is great, but I will be purchasing socks from other companies in the future.

title: Awesome product! Hood, scarf, and face mask in one!
text:
I am a petite woman, and this product fit me very well. Based on some of the other reviews, I was worried that it would be too big. It fits just right, and I think it would fit most people well. The trick is not to pull the hood too far forward unless you are using the drawstring to keep your face warm. The face mask potion can be held over your nose or pushed under the chin, making it versatile. It's made from a soft, warm fleece. In extreme windchill situations it might not be warm though - but I don't expect wind-proofing from a $10 product. It could probably be worn under another hood for extra warmth and wind resistance.

I have night classes, so I can't avoid long chilly walks. I think this product will help keep me warm and make my walks a lot more comfortable. Thanks!

I have the pewter and they're so pretty!  I'm now buying a pair in black.  Vionic shoes are the way to go!

I tell everyone with foot problems about these wonderful shoes and I intend to purchase more so I hope they don't discontinue them.

So be careful and check out your robe when you open the package and don't wait as I did for needing it ASAP.  Thanks.

I don't live near a mall so it took me several months before I was able to get to a mall for what I thought would be a battery change.  Turns out the watch itself was defective and so I had no choice but to throw it out and be out the cost of the watch.  I'm sticking with less expensive watches now so it doesn't hurt so much if it turns out the item is a DUD.  Anyway, happy birthday to me - not!

title: Not the worst, but also not the same old Asiscs
text: These are not the supportive asics gels of old. These new ones are quite the opposite in bads ways and good. While the older off-the-shelf models had ankle roll support, foot side support, a wide sole, and a confortable fit, these new ones forgo all that in favor of something else. For example, If you're overpronating, these shoes will expose this where as others just allow you to keep doing it. In spite of being available in assorted widths, these seemed a half size too tight. The low cut on the heel cup, a Asics signature, is still there which those with achilles tendinosis may welcome.

This bra is probably as good as any I have tried. It is also a good price.

title: Great style and comfort
text:

I am 5’4” and weigh about 170 lbs. I am large chested and have a belly. I ordered a large and it fit great. It even camouflages the belly.

The material is nice. It isn’t thin. It doesn’t wrinkle easily. The material is 95% cotton and 5% spandex. It has a nice stretch.

Care instructions say to wash cold. Do not bleach. Hang dry. Do not tumble dry. Do not iron. Do not dry clean. I did iron it and everything was fine.

title: Overall positive
text:
I really didn’t know what to rate this dress. Overall, I think it is a positive purchase.

I am 5’4” and weight about 170 lbs. I have a 43” bust. I did use the sizing chart to choose my size. I purchased a 2XL. Remember these are not sized for the USA. The dress definitely fit well.

I love the colors. I ordered the multicolored tie die dress with a flounce. The colors are very vibrant.

The fabric is 95% rayon and 5% spandex. It does have a stretch. The fabric seems a bit “swimsuit/dance costume “ to me. The hem and the flounce are finished by a serger stitch. Washing instructions say to wash with dark colors, separately; drip dry; low iron.

The waistband had elastic. When worn, there are just the gathers one would have with elastic. It definitely needs worn with a belt.

This would make a good clubbing outfit. It would definitely dry quickly if it gets wet.

title: Just plain awesome
text: Spent a week backpacking over the summer. And this product was a lifesaver. Its amazing how well it cools you down, and how it stays so cool for do long. And once it heats up... just snap it and its cold again. I will never hike in summertime without it.

title: BEST. SOCK. LINERS. EVER
text:
Bought these as sock liners to wear under my hiking socks for a week long backpacking trip.

For me, these are a complete game changer. After a week in the mountains, absolutely no blisters, and very happy feet. I've worn them since as regular socks, and they are by far the most comfortable pairs I own.

As for durability. These are toe socks. If you try to yank them on, you will eventually RIP them. You have to take the extra 2-3 seconds to make sure your toes go into the right holes. Just think of them like putting gloves on your feet, well, because that's exactly what they are.

title: Thank you Amazon!
text:
So difficult to find the right color (burgundy) baseball belt. After reviewing several contenders, we went with this on the brand alone- assuming it would be a quality belt.

We have not been disappointed. You get what you pay for, and sometimes the brand names are more expensive for a reason. This is one of those cases. You can be confident that when you buy this, it will be exactly what you are looking for and exactly what you need.

title: Great hiking boots
text: These are the most comfortable boots I own. I am an avid hiker/ backpacker and these boots have never let me down. They provide great support, especially as I have ankle issues, and they are solid and sturdy enough to.handle any terrain. Very light, and breathable, while still being essentially waterproof (I wouldn't submerge them, but morning dew, wet grass, puddles, etc are handled with ease and keep my feet nice and dry). These feel like a comfortable pair of tennis shoes even after miles and miles. There are more expensive boots our there, but the just aren't worth the extra money. These will do for anyone e but the most extreme outdoor type.

title: They do the job
text: Ordered the XL, and these were a little tight around the middle. Not unbearably so, but wish there was a velcro adjustment for the waste size. These were cheap, so I wasn't surprised by the so-so quality. Overall, these are worth it, but consider spending a bit more- especially if you plan on getting anything more than occasional use out of them. They just don't seem like they will hold up o er time.

title: Let's see if it can survive high school.
text: Bought this backpack to replace my son"s old Under Armour backpack, which finally succumbed to heavy High School student use. The backpack seems rugged enough, and well made, so it looks like it has potential. The old backpack lasted through Freshman year, and halfway through Sophomore year, so we were happy with that. At that point we bought a cheaper backpack, which didn't last a month- so, that is a very favourable comparison for Under Armour.

title: Good Product
text: I use these to practice dance routines at home which have carpet floors.  They help significantly to turn and eliminate friction, but it's obviously not going to be as good as socks on a tile floor.  I'd still recommend it because it works and stays on your shoe.

title: Gives legs nice appearance
text: I use these as part of a dance team costume and I like the way they look.  I'm 5'-3.5" and 125lbs. The Small/Medium fit fine.  The band waist band is not too tight.  My only complaint is that the foot pad extents to the sides of my foot and it's visible when wearing strappy shoes.

title: I'd only recommend for basic beginners or if you're looking for inexpensive practice shoes
text: The shoe was too big for the size and I found that the strap lengths around my foot would not hold my foot in place.  Also, I had to fix the buckles and put them on correctly.  The sole quality was a concern because after doing a couple spins to try the shoes out, I looked at the bottoms and the suede-like fuzz was disappearing and creating a mild bald spot. I own several pair of dancing shoes and primarily use them for latin dancing. There's no way that these shoes would hold up like my others .  Maybe if you're a beginner or need an extra pair of inexpensive practice shoes, this would be ok for you.

title: Totally Worth It.
text: I bought these because I was tired of buying the ten dollar water shoes that you can find at a pharmacy and having them last one or two wears.  These are fantastic!  Used them to go kayaking and then explore a beach.  The sand stayed out for a while but its inevitable that sand will enter your shoes.  I thought they were a little small at first, but I wore them with thin athletic socks and they were great in and out of the water.  As far as fit goes, I normally wear a 6-1/2 shoe and I bought a 7.  The 7 was a perfect fit.  If you normally like a little more room in your sneakers, then I'd recommend getting a whole size larger.

title: I got this to replace a gold band wedding ring ...

I have been wearing it for months and it still looks brand new. No scratches, and its still very shiny. Everyone thinks its white gold until I tell them its not.

title: Best bra you'll ever own
text: This is the best bra I have ever owned! It fits so well, and is very comfortable. Warner's also has great fabric styles and patterns in this bra. I bought my first one in a store but amazon by far has the best prices on this bra.

title: Decent.
text: Better than typical costume, not quite dress material. I’m 5’1 and it was about an inch longer than hoped but really no big deal. Worked out perfect for my costume.  Will be wearing it again.

title: Awesome cap!
text: My grandson loves this cap!  Soft and well made. He’s 16 months old with a good sized head and it fits perfect.

title: The jury is out on these. Updated.
text:
Will update after I wash the jumpsuit but first impressions are: the jumpsuit is large and baggy. You definitely need a shirt or tube top underneath or your boobs will show. :/. Right now it looks a little like a clown outfit but hoping I can shrink it a tad. I really want to love it. It’s lightweight, which I like and has pockets…yay!
UPDATE: washed on gentle cycle/cold water and dried on delicate cycle. The jumpsuit shrank slightly and it’s a perfect fit now. Will probably order 1 or 2 more with different patterns.

title: Love these!
text: Love them so much that I bought 3 more!  Comfy!  Has pockets that I love.  I wouldn’t say it’s a lot of tummy control but I think if they were super tight, I wouldn’t enjoy wearing them.

title: Cute and useful
text: I like this travel case. I don't use it for travel. I use it for my very fine jewelry and the print I got is really feminine and pretty. The top doesn't stay open very well but overall, it was worth the price.

title: Soft and compfy
text: This is a lovely red. Was a little expensive but I'm keeping it.

title: Too small
